      "term": "software",
      "snippet": "the nonprofit educational organization underlying the mag- gained 9,000 new subscribers from Point's failed other maga- zine, The Whole Earth Software Review, a casualty of the mid-'80s computer bust. By this merger it also acquired a multiple personality, and in a feverish amnesia of identity, CQ changed its name to Whole Earth Review after CQ #42."
